title: Holstin - Official Combat Gameplay Reveal Trailer
description:
Holstin is a retro-inspired psychological survival horror game developed by Sonka. Set in an isolated 1990s Polish lakeside town, players receive unsettling messages from a former coworker who is nowhere to be found. Players must venture into the town to not only find out the truth but to realize the fate of their coworker. The game uses Sonka's proprietary 2XD Rendering technology allowing for real-time lighting and a 3D camera amongst the pixel-art style. Players can also switch seamlessly between a third-person perspective for shooting and a classic top-down view for exploring. Holstin is coming to PlayStation, Xbox, Nintendo Switch, and PC with a demo available now via Steam.

#Holstin #Gameplay #Horror

title: PlayStation Portal Remote Player - Official Pre-Order Trailer
description:
PlayStation Portal Remote Player is a remote-play device specifically for PlayStation 5. Players can stream compatible games installed on their PS5 console with the use of Wi-Fi. The PlayStation Portal is fitted with DualSense features such as haptic feedback and adaptive triggers in supported games. The PlayStation Portal is available now for pre-order on PlayStation Direct.

#PlayStationPortal #PS5 #PlayStation5

title: Final Fantasy 16 - Official Free Update Trailer (Warning: Story Spoilers)
description:
*There are story spoilers in this trailer*

Square Enix developed Final Fantasy 16 has just unveiled a new free content update to the hit action RPG game. Players will now be able to have alternate costumes for the protagonists such as Burnt Black for Clive Rosefiled, Snow White for Jill Warrick, Icy Blue for Torgal, and more. The ability to change your blade appearance has also been added to the game. The free content update for Final Fantasy 16 is available now for PlayStation 5.

#FinalFantasy16 #FreeUpdate

title: Is This DeckHD Steam Deck Screen Upgrade Really Worth It? - Budget to Best
description:
The Steam Deck has been out for a while and has proven itself to be a worth portable solution for PC gaming. Though its 1280 x 800 pixel display works well enough and helps keep performance and power consumption well balanced, one might still crave a truly HD display. Luckily, DeckHD is just the solution such gamers have been waiting for. Is the DeckHD display upgrade for the Steam Deck worth it? Boasting a 1920 x 1200 pixel resolution and a higher 87% sRGB color accuracy over the stock Steam Deck display, Seth Macy takes you through the highs and lows of installing the new DeckHD display on his personal Steam Deck and lets you know whether or not diving in will be worth the splash.

#SteamDeck #DeckHD #BudgetToBest
